H World Group Ltd (HTHT.O) Price Target Base Case Updated Components EPS Investment Thesis Bull Base Bear Scenarios
Risk Reward for H World Group Ltd (HTHT.O) has been updated.

We updated our forecasts after the company's 2Q25 results beat our previous estimates due to better margins. We revised down 2025- 27E operating costs by \(1\%\) each. This is due to lower rental expenses as the company negotiated rental concessions from select landlords. We have increased EPS for 2025/26/27E by \(11\% /4\% /6\%\) on lower operating costs. As a result, our PT and base case have been revised up slightly by \(1\%\) to US \(43.5 / share. No changes to bull/bear cases.

Market leader with strong execution

One of China's largest and most widely recognized hotel chains, H World is reporting faster growth in number of hotels than peers. We believe the unit growth story remains intact because the pipeline is strong. We expect room growth to stay at \(>20\%\) p.a. Once RevPAR turns to positive growth, it will contribute a compounded positive impact to H World's margin and earnings growth, which we expect to occur in 2H26. EV/EBITDA valuation appears attractive.
Source: Refinitiv, Morgan Stanley Research

16x bull case 2025e EV/EBITDA

Positive RevPAR leading to operating leverage: RevPAR to grow \(13\%\) above the 2024 level in 2025 with annual gross unit growth of 2,600 hotels domestically. Group EBITDA margin including DH surpasses 2019's level in 2025.
14x base case 2025e EV/EBITDA

Fast unit growth with consolidation power, high operating leverage: Sustained premium brand image enhances rollout of franchise business. Steady growth by gross additions of 2,400 hotels annually in 2025- 27.

Downcycle: Because of high operating leverage, RevPAR decline has a significant negative impact on L&O business EBITDA. In this scenario, blended RevPAR widens its decline in 2025 and hotel gross openings fall to 1,700 a year from 2025.

Overweight (O). The stock's total return is expected to exceed the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.

Equal-weight (E). The stock's total return is expected to be in line with the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.

Not-Rated (NR). Currently the analyst does not have adequate conviction about the stock's total return relative to the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.

Underweight (U). The stock's total return is expected to be below the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.
